Find all values of \(x\) such that \(x-$A\), \(x+$A\), and \($B x -$A\) form a
geometric sequence.  Give your answers in increasing order.

$BR
$BR
\(x\) can equal \{ans_rule(10)\} or \{ans_rule(10)\}.



END_TEXT
## Closes a block of text

